records.addlTxt:
10:44 AM Defendant Rani Bell in court, in custody, with attorney John Paul Marchan.   Andrea M Will appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case called for plea and sentencing.
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 3.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Count 4 is Dismissed and read in.
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations.
Defendant makes statement to the court.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE OF:

2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 0 days) - Consecutive to any other sentence being served; 
  -  1 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  1 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. 
Defendant is  eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*Absolute Sobriety; 
*No Use or Possession of synthetic drugs or CBD products;
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*No contact with:  Victim Business; 
*DNA sample to be provided;
*Domestic Violence Counseling through a State Certified Batterers Intervention Program such as  Alliance Counseling or Family Services of Waukesha;
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores).
*Attend at least 2 self help meetings per week. 
*Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate.

RESTITUTION:  $0 ;

COURT COSTS:  Court finds Defendant indigent and waives costs. 

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

*Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
